comments.body: Note: added some new common types that will be shared between some `fp` functions

I'm surprised this behaves differently than `Dictionary<any> | NumericDictionary<any>`.

If you simplify this to just:

```ts
type AnyKindOfDictionary = Dictionary<{} | null | undefined> | NumericDictionary<{} | null | undefined>;
```

does it still work?
That does work. I clearly don't quite understand the type system of TypeScript yet. Every time I think I got it, I run into something like this.
